body:
{{champion:106}} 

His kit is BORING.

Volibear, to me, feels like the only champion Riot made where they said &quot;People will play/buy this no matter what, we don&#039;t have to try in making his kit&quot; and made one of the most bland designs I&#039;ve ever seen.

* Passive- A min-mundo ult. This really is just a &quot;second life&quot; punishment for hitting him down. Why does a bear have a regeneration mechanic? Because &quot;A bruiser/tank needs some manner of sustain&quot;.
* Q- MS boost plus a flip. There&#039;s no creativity to this skill, it was a sandwich between Garen Q but with a Singed flip. The animation is cool but it feels quite unsatisfying to just run up and flip one person. &quot;A bruiser/tank needs some kind of hard CC and gap closer&quot;
* W- Bonus AS with an execute. The &quot;We want him to jungle&quot; skill. Slap them three times, bite, that&#039;s about the sum of it. &quot;A bruiser/tank needs the ability to jungle and have threat&quot;
* E- AoE slow with a fear component. The fear is an interesting part that separates it from just another generic slow...but outside of that, it&#039;s still kind of bland. A short AoE slow where the minion fear doesn&#039;t really come into play. &quot;A bruiser needs sticking power&quot;
* R- The actual interesting part of his kit. Volibear&#039;s thunder claws really make for some neat builds and splitpushing/teamfight potential. If there was one skill I&#039;d want preserved in some manner, be it an ultimate or turned into a basic, it&#039;s this.

Yes, you could apply my arguments to almost any champion but Volibear just feels unsatisfying. His kit doesn&#039;t feel particularly unique outside of his ultimate and he really doesn&#039;t bring much to the table in terms of meat shield or raw damage. With a concept like a thundering armored bear, Riot really let this guy fall into obscurity and didn&#039;t give him anything interesting. Hell, how many people actually KNOW Volibear exists? Sure he gets to the job done but he&#039;s so forgettable kit-wise that most just pick him for the sake of aesthetic if they really like bears.

I hope Riot has some plan for Volibear because he needs a stronger gameplay identity. This mishmash tank bruiser thing is a really gross holdover from S2.
